I have both python2.7 and python3.2 installed in Ubuntu 16.04

$ sudo apt-get install python3-setuptools

$ sudo easy_install3 pip
$ sudo pip-3.2 install numpy
$ sudo easy_install3 pip
$ sudo pip-3.5 install numpy
        or
$ sudo pip3.5 install numpy
## Check Version 
change the Python version in Jupyter Notebook or Spider or on terminal
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
np.__version__
pd.__version__


# For jupyter, change the kernel i.e from python3 to python2 and vice verse

$ python3 -m pip install ipykernel
